{
  "stem": "19837.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we saw the planes, sh, and heard them flying real low.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Japanese had put us-- had put the Navy-- Navy yard-- we didn't know they had weapons or ammunitions there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had no idea.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we saw the Japanese playing baseball.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We didn't know what it was and somebody knew that and said, oh, that's like the Americans do, they play baseball.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We saw them.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But when the planes started flying over, we knew they flew-- Americans flew to Japan.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when they came back, we heard that, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then towards the end of the war, they tried-- they bombed Shanghai, the Americans bombed Shanghai.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And like I said, we had no idea that-- why do they want-- what do they want from Hongkew, from us?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So one day, they dropped a bomb there and 30 people, Jewish people, died and a lot of Chinese.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And after that-- before that, we didn't have any problem with Chinese people, but after that we were really buddies because our people and their people all-- everyone helped each other.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so Henry was six years old-- or what, '38, five years old.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He said, you told me the Americans are our friends.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "What do-- why do they bomb Hongkew?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I said, well, they don't know we live here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "What can you explain a five-year-old?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "What I found out now is also that the Americans save in, in-- if you fight a war on so many fronts, how can you take and think about the handful of people there or the handful of people there we don't want to hurt?",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They had their targets and that's what they did.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "What was it like for you once the bombings began?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, everybody stayed home then.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
